-- Shares in South Africa Climb as Trading Resumes, Paced by Anglo, BHP, MTN
-- Ana Monteiro
-- 2010-07-27T13:31:46Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-27/south-african-shares-gain-after-trading-resumes-paced-by-anglo-billiton.html

          
          
             South African shares gained for a
sixth day after trading resumed as a technical glitch was
resolved.  
 The JSE/FTSE Africa All Share Index rose 258.67, or 0.9
percent, to 28,757.67 as of 3:25 p.m. in Johannesburg. Trading
resumed at 3:20 p.m., with BHP Billiton Ltd., Anglo American Plc
and MTN Group Ltd. pacing gains, Bloomberg data show. Operations
halted at about 9:26 a.m.  
          
          


  


        